I read with interest the several posts concerning how people on here are seeming to complain a lot and not posting so called "good posts".  So here's the challenge.  Those of you who are fed up with the complaints, then how about you put up a well thought out post that documents all the current advantages of the Sorc.  I mean there are currently so many, it should be easy, it is easy, isn't it?  So give it a try.  What makes the Sorc unique and/or better than any other class in Albion? What one thing or multiple things do we do better than any other class that makes us viable and necessary?<P>Something that Mythic should take note of, when EVERYONE starts complaining, there is probably, most likely, a problem.<P>--------------------<P>Badea<BR>Sorceress Bedevere
